</p>
<p>There are two ways to hook into an event: via a listener or a subscriber. They're
really the same thing, but I think subscribers are cooler. To hook one up, make this class
implement <code>EventSubscriberInterface</code> - the one from Symfony. Now, hit cmd+n - or go
to the the Code-&gt;Generate menu - select "Implement Methods" and select <code>getSubscribedEvents</code>.
That's a fast way to generate the <em>one</em> method from <code>EventSubscriberInterface</code> that
we need to fill in:</p>
<p><div class="code-block-wrapper" data-code-block-guid="d9226344a4">
    <div class="meta">
        <div class="actions">
            <span class="fa fa-clipboard js-activate-clipboard" data-toggle="tooltip" title="Copy Code" data-placement="top"></span>
        </div>
        <div class="info">
