<p>So once we tell Symfony about this class, whenever an exception is thrown,
Symfony will call this method. And when it does, it'll pass us an <code>$event</code> argument
object. But what type of object is that? Hold cmd - or control for Windows and Linux - 
and click the <code>EXCEPTION</code> constant. The documentation <em>above</em> it tells us that we'll
be passed a <code>GetResponseForExceptionEvent</code> object. Close that class and type-hint
the event argument. Don't forget your <code>use</code> statement:</p>
