<p>That tag is enough to tell Symfony about our subscriber - it'll take care of the
rest.</p>
<p>Head back to our test where we send invalid JSON and expect the 400 status code.
This already worked before, but the response was HTML, so the next assert - for a JSON response
with a <code>type</code> property - has been failing hard. Actually, I totally messed up that
assert earlier - make sure you're asserting a <code>type</code> key, not <code>test</code>:</p>
